# Pre-publish leak-scan allowlist for the Ben example agent.
# Each entry is an extended-regex; matching scan lines are EXEMPT. Real leaks
# must NEVER be allowlisted — review additions like code.

# why: RFC-2606 reserved example domain. The config.yaml email field ships with
# "you@example.com" as an obvious, non-real placeholder for the operator to
# replace. example.com / example.org / example.net can never resolve to a real
# inbox, so this is a documented false positive, not operator PII.
[a-z]+@example\.(com|org|net)
